SIMPLE: dearly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dearly
<hw>Dear"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a dear manner;
with affection; heartily; earnestly; <as>as, to love one
<ex>dearly</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At a high rate or price; grievously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He buys his mistress <qex>dearly</qex> with his throne.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exquisitely.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dearn</ent>⟦br⟧
